## 🗺️ Development Phases

---

### Phase 1 — Car Rental Module
**Goal:** Give the business a complete car rental booking flow parallel to the car wash.
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the biggest next feature. Design the data model carefully before building.

#### 1.1 Car Fleet Management (Backend)
- [ ] Create `carModel.js` with fields: `name`, `brand`, `category`, `plateNumber`, `pricePerDay`, `pricePerHour`, `fuelType`, `transmission`, `seats`, `images[]`, `status` (Available / Rented / Maintenance)
- [ ] Create `rentalBookingModel.js` with: `car`, `renterName`, `contactNumber`, `email`, `pickupDate`, `returnDate`, `totalDays`, `totalPrice`, `paymentStatus`, `status`
- [ ] Create `carController.js` and `rentalBookingController.js` (CRUD)

#### 1.2 Public Rental Booking Page (Frontend)
- [ ] New page `/rent` showing the car fleet as a visual card grid
- [ ] Date range picker (Pickup → Return date selector)
- [ ] Live price calculator (`totalDays × pricePerDay`)
- [ ] Confirm booking page with renter details form
- [ ] reCAPTCHA protection (same as carwash form)

#### 1.3 Employee: Rental Dashboard Tab
- [ ] New tab in the Employee Dashboard sidebar: "Car Rentals"
- [ ] Table showing all Rental Bookings (similar to the current car wash table)
- [ ] Modal for viewing/editing rental details, including car assignment

#### 1.4 Car Availability Calendar
- [ ] Show a monthly calendar view per car
- [ ] Block out dates that are already booked
- [ ] Prevent double-booking the same vehicle

---

### Phase 2 — Admin Panel
**Goal:** Give the shop owner full control over everything without needing a developer.

> [!NOTE]
> The Admin role should be a **separate account type** from regular employees. Add a `role` field to the employee model: `admin | employee`.

#### 2.1 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- [ ] Add `role: { type: String, enum: ['admin', 'employee'], default: 'employee' }` to [employeeModel.js](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/models/employeeModel.js)
- [ ] Create `adminMiddleware.js` to protect admin-only routes
- [ ] Add admin-only navigation links in the Dashboard sidebar

#### 2.2 Price List Manager (Admin → Pricing)
- [ ] Table UI showing all vehicle types with editable price fields for each service
- [ ] An "Add New Vehicle" form to insert new rows into the [Pricing](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/controllers/pricingController.js#29-50) collection
- [ ] A "Delete Vehicle" option with a confirmation popup
- [ ] All changes write directly to MongoDB, and all public pages automatically reflect the new prices

#### 2.3 Employee Manager (Admin → Employees)
- [ ] Table of all employee accounts
- [ ] Ability to Create / Suspend / Delete employee accounts
- [ ] Assign roles (`admin` or `employee`)
- [ ] View last login timestamps

#### 2.4 Car Fleet Manager (Admin → Cars)
- [ ] Add, edit, or archive cars in the fleet
- [ ] Upload car images
- [ ] Mark a car as "Under Maintenance" to remove it from rental listings

#### 2.5 Business Settings
- [ ] Shop hours (start/end time) editable — dynamically updates the time-slot selector
- [ ] Max capacity per time slot (currently hardcoded to 3) editable
- [ ] Armor add-on flat price editable (currently hardcoded to ₱100)

---

### Phase 3 — Dashboard Analytics & Reporting
**Goal:** Give management real-time visibility into business performance.

#### 3.1 Overview Widgets (Top of Dashboard)
- [ ] **Earnings Today** — Sum of `totalPrice` for `Completed` bookings with today's date
- [ ] **Bookings Today** — Count of bookings for today
- [ ] **Pending Approval** — Count of `Pending` status bookings
- [ ] **Cars Available** — Count of cars with [Available](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/frontend/src/utils/priceList.js#24-36) status

#### 3.2 Revenue Charts
- [ ] Weekly earnings bar chart (using Chart.js or Recharts)
- [ ] Monthly booking volume line chart
- [ ] Top services by revenue (pie chart: Wash vs Wax vs Engine vs Armor)
- [ ] Top vehicle categories by booking count

#### 3.3 PDF Reporting
- [ ] "Generate Report" button which exports a `.pdf` of the current month's earnings
- [ ] Individual booking receipt/invoice (PDF) employee can print and hand to customer

#### 3.4 Export to CSV
- [ ] Export the filtered booking table to a `.csv` spreadsheet
- [ ] Useful for manual bookkeeping in Excel / Google Sheets

---

### Phase 4 — Data Security Hardening
**Goal:** Make the system production-grade and protect customer data.

> [!CAUTION]
> Never skip security steps before going live. A data breach in the Philippines is governed by the **Data Privacy Act (RA 10173)** and can result in heavy fines.

#### 4.1 Authentication Improvements
- [ ] **Refresh Token Rotation** — Add a `refreshToken` (long-lived, stored in `httpOnly` cookie) paired with a short-lived `accessToken` (15 minutes). This prevents token theft.
- [ ] **Password complexity rules** — Minimum 8 chars, uppercase, number, symbol
- [ ] **Account lockout** — Temporarily lock an account after 5 failed login attempts (using `loginAttempts` + `lockUntil` fields on the employee model)
- [ ] **Password reset flow** — "Forgot Password" email link using `nodemailer` + a time-limited reset token stored in MongoDB

#### 4.2 Data Sanitization
- [ ] Install and use `express-validator` on ALL POST/PATCH endpoints to validate and sanitize incoming data
- [ ] Add `mongo-sanitize` to prevent NoSQL injection attacks
- [ ] Add `hpp` middleware to prevent HTTP Parameter Pollution

#### 4.3 Rate Limiting
- [ ] Install `express-rate-limit`
- [ ] Apply strict limits on the booking and login endpoints (e.g., 10 requests per 15 minutes per IP)
- [ ] Apply looser limits on public GET endpoints (e.g., pricing, availability)

#### 4.4 Security Headers
- [ ] Install `helmet` — sets secure HTTP headers automatically (X-Frame-Options, Content-Security-Policy, etc.)
- [ ] Configure CORS precisely for production domain only

#### 4.5 Customer Data Privacy
- [ ] Add a **Data Retention Policy** — automatically delete booking records older than 2 years using a scheduled MongoDB TTL index or a cron job
- [ ] Add a **Privacy Policy** page to the public site
- [ ] Add a clear consent checkbox on the booking form

#### 4.6 HTTPS & SSL
- [ ] Ensure the production server forces HTTPS (handled by Azure App Service, but verify)
- [ ] Verify all cookies have `secure: true` and `sameSite: 'strict'` in production

---

### Phase 5 — Database Management & Reliability
**Goal:** Ensure data is safe, performant, and recoverable.

> [!WARNING]
> Do **not** rely on the free MongoDB Atlas tier for production. Upgrade to at least M10 for dedicated cluster resources and automatic backups.

#### 5.1 Indexes
- [ ] Add MongoDB indexes on frequently queried fields:
  - [Booking](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/controllers/bookingController.js#21-36): `bookingTime`, `status`, `createdAt`
  - [Notification](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/controllers/notificationController.js#3-12): `isRead`, `createdAt`
  - [Employee](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/frontend/src/pages/employee/EmployeeDashboard.jsx#141-364): `email` (already unique, but ensure index exists)
  - [Pricing](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/controllers/pricingController.js#29-50): `vehicleType` (already unique)

#### 5.2 Automated Backups
- [ ] Enable **MongoDB Atlas Continuous Backup** (or configure nightly snapshots)
- [ ] Set up a backup retention window of at least 7 days

#### 5.3 Database Seeding & Migration Scripts
- [ ] Create a `scripts/seed.js` file for re-seeding the Pricing collection on a fresh deployment
- [ ] Create migration scripts for any future schema changes (e.g., adding a new field to `bookingModel`)

#### 5.4 Soft Deletes
- [ ] Instead of hard-deleting records, add `isArchived: Boolean` + `archivedAt: Date` to key models
- [ ] This preserves historical data for reporting and compliance

#### 5.5 Mongoose Connection Pooling
- [ ] Set `maxPoolSize` in the Mongoose connection options to handle concurrent requests under load

#### 5.6 Database Monitoring
- [ ] Set up **MongoDB Atlas Alerts** for: high CPU, connection spikes, replica lag
- [ ] Review slow query logs monthly using Atlas Performance Advisor

---

### Phase 6 — Production Infrastructure & Launch
**Goal:** A stable, monitored, and maintainable production deployment.

#### 6.1 Environment Management
- [ ] Use separate [.env](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/.env) files per environment: `.env.development`, `.env.staging`, `.env.production`
- [ ] Never commit [.env](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/.env) files to Git (enforce with [.gitignore](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/.gitignore))
- [ ] Store all secrets in Azure App Service Environment Variables (not code)

#### 6.2 CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` to automatically build and deploy on `git push` to `main`
- [ ] Add a lint/test step before deployment to catch errors early

#### 6.3 Error Monitoring
- [ ] Integrate **Sentry** (free tier available) for automatic error capture in both frontend and backend
- [ ] Set up email alerts for critical backend crashes

#### 6.4 SMS / Email Notifications to Customers
- [ ] When a booking status changes to `Confirmed`, automatically send the customer an SMS (via **Semaphore** — Philippine SMS gateway) or email (via **Resend** or **SendGrid**)
- [ ] Include booking details: name, service, time, batch ID

#### 6.5 Performance Optimization
- [ ] Enable Vite's production build (`npm run build`) and serve the static bundle through Azure CDN
- [ ] Enable gzip compression on the Express server (`compression` middleware)
- [ ] Lazy-load heavy components in React (e.g., the Dashboard, the booking modal)

#### 6.6 Accessibility & SEO
- [ ] Run a Lighthouse audit and fix all critical issues
- [ ] Add OpenGraph meta tags for social sharing previews
- [ ] Ensure all images have `alt` attributes
- [ ] Implement `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt`

---

### Phase 7 — Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Integration
**Goal:** Transform the Sandigan platform from a booking tool into a complete business management suite.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Because ERP modules deal with highly sensitive data (payroll, taxes, customer details), this phase **requires** Phase 2 (Admin Panel) and Phase 4 (Security Hardening) to be 100% completed first.

#### 7.1 Finance & Accounting Systems (Ledger)
- [ ] **Expense Tracking:** Create an `expensesModel.js` to log daily shop purchases (soap, water bills, rent, equipment).
- [ ] **Profit & Loss (P&L):** Deduct `expenses` from `booking.totalPrice` dynamically to show real-time Net Profit on the Admin Dashboard.
- [ ] **Invoicing & Taxation:** Generate official BIR-compliant automated receipts and tax deduction reports.

#### 7.2 Human Resource Information Systems (HRIS)
- [ ] **Employee Portal (Detailers):** Expand [employeeModel.js](file:///c:/Visual%20Studio%20Projects/Sandigan-Carwash-Web-app/Sandigan/backend/models/employeeModel.js) to include `hourlyRate`, `schedule`, and `status`.
- [ ] **Timesheets & Payroll:** Implement a Clock-In/Clock-Out system. Automatically calculate weekly payroll based on hours worked + commission per car washed.
- [ ] **Performance Tracking:** Tie the `detailer` field on bookings to an employee's profile to track who washes the most cars fastest.

#### 7.3 Inventory & Supply Chain Systems
- [ ] **Stock Registry:** Create an `inventoryModel.js` mapping all physical assets (Car Shampoo, Armor All, Engine Degreaser, Microfibers).
- [ ] **Automated Depletion:** Every time a "Wash + Armor" booking is completed, automatically deduct `0.5 Liters` of Armor All from the database.
- [ ] **Low Stock Alerts:** Use the Notification system to alert the Admin when a supply drops below a minimum threshold strictly needing reorder.

#### 7.4 Sales, CRM & Customer Data
- [ ] **Customer Profiles:** Every time a new `phoneNumber` or `email` books a service, automatically create a `customerModel.js` record.
- [ ] **Loyalty Program:** Track total visits per customer. Automatically apply a 10% discount on their 10th car wash.
- [ ] **SMS Marketing:** Use the Semaphore integration to blast promo codes to customers who haven't booked in the last 60 days.

#### 7.5 Project & Operations Management
- [ ] **Bay Scheduling (Gantt Chart):** Visual timeline showing which physical Carwash Bay is occupied at what time, minimizing physical traffic jams.
- [ ] **Maintenance Logs:** Track maintenance schedules for pressure washers, vacuums, and the Rental Fleet (Phase 1).

