## 🧱 System Architecture (Current + Target)

```mermaid
graph TD
    Customer["👤 Customer (Browser)"]
    Employee["🧑‍💼 Employee (Browser)"]
    Admin["👑 Admin (Browser)"]

    subgraph Frontend["React Frontend (Vite)"]
        PublicPages["Public Pages\n(Landing, Book, Rent)"]
        EmployeeDash["Employee Dashboard"]
        AdminPanel["Admin Panel (Phase 2)"]
    end

    subgraph Backend["Express.js API (Node.js)"]
        AuthMiddleware["JWT + CSRF Middleware"]
        BookingCtrl["Booking Controller"]
        RentalCtrl["Rental Controller (Phase 1)"]
        PricingCtrl["Pricing Controller"]
        NotifCtrl["Notification Controller"]
        EmpCtrl["Employee Controller"]
        SocketIO["Socket.io (Real-time)"]
    end

    subgraph Database["MongoDB Atlas"]
        BookingColl["bookings"]
        RentalColl["rentalBookings (Phase 1)"]
        PricingColl["pricing"]
        NotifColl["notifications"]
        EmpColl["employees (HRIS Phase 7)"]
        CarColl["cars (Phase 1)"]
        ERPColl["expenses, inventory, customers (Phase 7)"]
    end

    Customer --> PublicPages
    Employee --> EmployeeDash
    Admin --> AdminPanel

    PublicPages -->|HTTPS + CSRF| Backend
    EmployeeDash -->|HTTPS + JWT + CSRF| Backend
    AdminPanel -->|HTTPS + JWT + Admin Role| Backend

    Backend --> Database
    SocketIO <-->|WebSocket| EmployeeDash
```

---

## 📋 Recommended Build Order

| Priority | Phase | Reason |
|----------|-------|--------|
| 🥇 First | **Phase 4.3 & 4.4** (Rate Limiting + Helmet) | Cheapest and fastest win for security. Do now. |
| 🥈 Second | **Phase 2.1 & 2.2** (RBAC + Price Manager) | Releases the owner from needing a developer to update prices. |
| 🥉 Third | **Phase 3.1** (Dashboard Widgets) | Fast to build, high business value for daily operations. |
| 4th | **Phase 1** (Car Rental) | Largest feature, needs careful planning. |
| 5th | **Phase 6.4** (SMS/Email Notifications) | Improves customer experience significantly. |
| 6th | **Phase 5** (DB Management) | Needed before heavy scaling. |
| 7th | **Phase 7** (Core ERP Modules) | The ultimate expansion. Requires all prior admin and security foundations to be solid. |

